grades_mod <-grades %>% 
  mutate(
   scores_rounded = 
     case_when(
    `Letter Grade` == "O" ~ 10,
    `Letter Grade` == "A+" ~ 9,
    `Letter Grade` == "A" ~ 8,
    `Letter Grade` == "B+" ~ 7,
    `Letter Grade` == "B" ~ 6,
    `Letter Grade` == "C" ~ 5,
    `Letter Grade` == "P" ~ 3,
  
  ) )

Examining Data

.

##
grades_mod %>% 
gf_histogram(~scores_rounded,
  fill = ~Degree,
  alpha = 0.5,
) %>%
  gf_vline(xintercept = ~ mean(scores_rounded)) %>%
  gf_labs(
    title = "Histograms of Score Distributions vs Degree",
    x = "Scores", y = "Count"
  ) %>%
  gf_text(7 ~ (mean(scores_rounded) + 2),
    label = "Overall Mean"
  ) %>%
  gf_refine(guides(fill = guide_legend(title = "Scores")))

.

##
grades_mod %>% 
gf_boxplot(

  fill = ~Degree,
  alpha = 0.5
) %>%
  gf_vline(xintercept = ~ mean(scores_rounded)) %>%
  gf_labs(

ANOVA

.

grades_anova <- aov(scores_rounded ~ Degree, data = grades_mod)

.

#
supernova::pairwise(grades_anova,
  correction = "Bonferroni", # Try "Tukey"
  alpha = 0.05, # 95% CI calculation
  var_equal = TRUE, # We'll see
  plot = TRUE
)

Checking ANOVA Assumptions

Checks for Normality

.

shapiro.test(x = grades_mod$scores_rounded)

    Shapiro-Wilk normality test

data:  grades_mod$scores_rounded
W = 0.9034, p-value = 5.762e-06

.

grades_mod %>%
  group_by(Degree) %>%
  group_modify(~ .x %>%
    select(scores_rounded) %>%
    as_vector() %>%
    shapiro.test() %>%
    broom::tidy())
# A tibble: 3 × 4
# Groups:   Degree [3]

ANOVA using Permutation Test

.

observed_infer <-
  grades_mod %>%
  specify(scores_rounded ~ Degree) %>%
  hypothesise(null = "independence") %>%
  calculate(stat = "F")
observed_infer
Response: scores_rounded (numeric)
Explanatory: Degree (factor)
Null Hypothesis: independence
# A tibble: 1 × 1
   stat
  <dbl>
1  2.87

.

null_dist_infer <- grades_mod %>%
  specify(scores_rounded ~ Degree) %>%
  hypothesise(null = "independence") %>%
  generate(reps = 4999, type = "permute") %>%
  calculate(stat = "F")
##
